						<summary>

						<p>On the pedestal of Parśvanātha image (1) in the Brahmadēva temple.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">1400 A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>It states that the image of Parśvanātha was consecrated by Lakshmīsēna-bhaṭṭāraka and the basadi was constructed by Laḷiyādēvi, the great-grand mother of Sēnarasa and a disciple of Vīranandisiddhānta-Chakravarti of Mūla-saṁgha, Dēsiya-gaṇa and Pustaka-gachchha. Sculptor Jinnōja carved the image.</p>						

						<p>It is dated Śaka 1(3)22, Vikrama, Chaitra Śu. 12 Monday which corresponds to 1400 A.D., March 8. [The month Chaitra was adhika].</p>						

						</summary>
